WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.240
So what is your name, where are you from, and what are you doing at this competition?

00:04.240 --> 00:08.680
My name is Jeremiah Dibley and I'm here just to be a chaperone for the students

00:08.680 --> 00:13.280
who are competing in this event and just enjoying my time in Florida looking at

00:13.280 --> 00:17.240
all the cool scenery and being here at NASA that's pretty cool. What's it like

00:17.240 --> 00:20.800
watching the students compete in this competition? Well they're very focused,

00:20.800 --> 00:25.400
very driven, very talented, and so it's inspiring. I'm a teacher by trade so I

00:25.400 --> 00:30.040
just love to see kids working and learning without being told to do so. I

00:30.040 --> 00:32.720
mean they just want it and they're showing off their talents and their

00:32.720 --> 00:36.440
their collaborative skills and their soft skills too so it's just cool to see

00:36.440 --> 00:42.480
them. You said you brought some kids here right? How have you seen them grow or

00:42.480 --> 00:47.720
change due to this competition? Yeah they're they're conquering some fears

00:47.720 --> 00:50.720
they're just being real courageous and interacting with people from other

00:50.720 --> 00:54.920
cultures who speak other languages who maybe are are just different from them

00:54.920 --> 00:58.400
in every way and so it's cool to see them break out of their shell and be

00:58.400 --> 01:02.960
confident. And how did you feel about the speaker John Bates yesterday? I thought

01:02.960 --> 01:08.840
he did a great job of sharing some of those soft skill priorities as we work

01:08.840 --> 01:13.080
together to solve problems whether it's space or anything else. Working with

01:13.080 --> 01:16.000
other people and being able to communicate effectively and just keep

01:16.000 --> 01:20.320
people's attention is just part of relationship building and you can just

01:20.320 --> 01:24.320
see how he shared that with with the kids and helping them understand how

01:24.320 --> 01:29.080
relationships are important in solving problems. Awesome thank you.

